caption.p: COVID-19 pregnant patients: summary of publications through April 5, 2020. abnl = abnormal; ARDS = acute respiratory distress syndrome; COVID-19 = coronavirus disease 2019; CT = computerized tomography; CXR = chest x-ray; ECMO = extracorporeal membrane oxygenation; GA = gestational age; Ig = immunoglobulin; IUGR = intrauterine growth restriction; LBW = low birth weight; LGA = large for gestational age; neg = negative; NND = neonatal death; NP = nasopharyngeal (swab); PCR = polymerase chain reaction; PTL = preterm labor; pos = positive; RDS = respiratory distress syndrome; SGA = small for gestational age; SOB = shortness of breath.
